criteria.textblock:
        The inclusion criteria:

          1. the patient who suffer from first stroke was admitted to the stroke center of National
             Taiwan University Hospital (NTUH) within 3 days of onset

          2. National Institutes of Health Stroke Scale (NIHSS) scores ranging from 5 to 25

          3. totally activity of daily living independent before stroke onset;

          4. between 40-80 years old;

          5. stroke with unilateral hemiparesis lesions confirmed by magnetic resonance imaging
             (MRI) or computed tomography (CT), with vascular lesions verified by magnetic
             resonance angiography (MRA);

          6. a cortical or subcortical infarction or hemorrhage;

          7. no other peripheral or central nervous system dysfunction;

          8. no active inflammation or pathologic changes in the joints;

          9. no active medical problems.

        The exclusion criteria:

          1. medical conditions unrelated to the cerebrovascular accident but which had affected
             walking performance

          2. other cognitive, emotional, or behavioral impairments that result in insufficient
             comprehension, understanding, or collaboration

          3. medical problems potentially adversely affected by electric stimulation

          4. had skin conditions, or had allergies etc.
